Date: Sun, 27 Jul 2025 22:06:45 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 8/8] QSDK: CP: hostapd: ATF: Add airtime distribution logic

Distribute airtime to all peers and ssid/ssid group
based on the configuration.

The distribution can be in 3 ways:
	1. when ssid config is enabled.
	2. when ssid_group is enabled.
	3. default, when dynamic atf is enabled (i.e., no ssid/ssid
group configuration)

Candidate list assumptions:
	1. In case of ssid config, each configured ssid will have
	   its own group and unconfigured ssids will be in default group.
	2. In case of ssid group, one or more ssid will be a group,
	   if unconfigured they will be in default group.

So, in both ssid config/ssid group case, group will be the entity on
which algorithm runs.

The following would be the distribution algorithm:
	1. If no peer is associated, no need for any distribution. Skip.
	2. For each group except default group, calculate for all the peer associated with
	   the group:
		a. configured peers calculation
			peer_airtime = ((group_airtime *
					 peer_configured_airtime)/ 100)
		b. For unconfigured peers:

			peer_airtime_calculation = residual_group_airtime/
						   no_of_unconfigured_peers

		Distribute equally the residual group airtime among unconfigured group clients
	3. Now assign the residual airtime equally to the default-group
peers.

Build the group config, peer config and wmm config expected by the
driver.

While building the peer config to driver consider below flags:
	A full update – Send about all the peers associated.
		1. When there is a reboot, and the first client gets associated.
		2. When atf_commit command is issued in between two command runs.
	A partial update – This will happen only in the following scenarios.
		The clients which get associated
		When a particular client gets disconnected and connected again.

Signed-off-by: Harshitha Prem <hprem@qti.qualcomm.com>
